summary: You don't know what happens when you die? You have any ideas? Your eyes will just... empty, and your soul goes in. People think...
caption: You don’t know what happens when you die? You have any ideas? Your eyes will just… empty, and your soul goes in. People think that your soul or personality, whatever, leaves the body when you die. I swear, it just goes further in. It falls so far in and just becomes so small that it can’t control your body anymore. It’s just in there, dying forever.

summary: I'm seeing all the people on Twitter from the UK flip out because Killing Eve is gonna air there soon (or has recently started)...
body: I’m seeing all the people on Twitter from the UK flip out because Killing Eve is gonna air there soon (or has recently started) and I’m just honestly surprised so many people actually wait to watch like that when you can get it online. I mean, obviously the viewership is super important and I’m hella glad for it (I’m sure some have already seen it too) but still I can’t imagine waiting for a show that spectacular and hyped-up when the Internet makes it so easy lol.

answer: The most recently written sentences of my latest project: She doesn’t know when Oksana had left; for all she knows, it could’ve been as soon as she’d fallen into dreams.
